<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-02-27</DATELINE><TITLE>Macroeconomic Effect of Infectious Disease Outbreaks</TITLE><BODY>This article highlights the important macroeconomic effects of communicable disease outbreaks, focusing especially on evidence from computablegeneral equilibrium analyses. It illustrates how, in particular, labor supply and behavior change effects have been estimated using retrospective analysis and macroeconomic models.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>